
**What I like? (sorted by best at the top)**

1. Hamish streams and videos - this just has to be numero uno ü´°, he''s just really really friendly and positive, he''s the face of this game right now and he''s doing a great job.
2. The progression system and leagues, that phase before hitting eternals feels very clear in terms of game progression, milestones are visible, gear upgrades, finishing a capstone in time and moving on to the next difficulty simply feels good and rewarding.
3. It may feel dumb to ‚Äòlike‚Äô such a simple thing, but the Interrupt system is just amazing to me, no idea if there are other games that has implemented this in a similar/exact way or not, personally I didn‚Äôt see something like that anywhere else. the simplicity of me marking a target so everyone now knows ‚Äúokie, this one is taken care of‚Äù is just awesome.
4. The dungeons, the art, boss fights, really really well done, I specifically like the capstone. I especially love Cithrel‚Äôs Fall and Wraithtide, I dig the fact that there are 3 bosses and I get to choose the order I get to tackle them, I can build my route the way I want.
5. The patch cadence feels good, feels like the game is getting more than decent attention on a weekly basis.
6. Attention to details, I have a bunch of examples, but let‚Äôs pick just one, to me, things like the hidden holiday bear mount shows the love for the game by the devs.

**What I dislike and would love to see getting addressed and improved**  
**(again sorted by my highest priority at the top)**

1. No ‚Äòbad luck‚Äô protection in legendaries, in my eyes, this should be a top priority and relatively easy to address. legendaries have huge impact on your gameplay and damage/healing, it feels really really bad not getting your ‚Äòneeded‚Äô legendary. For example, my main is Helena, I had amazing luck and got the exact legendary that I‚Äôve wanted after a few champion dungeons runs.. it felt great. but on my Mara, the only viable legendary right now are the boots, the boots provide incredible gains to energy regeneration and damage, the two other legendaries are trash in comparison‚Ä¶. And I‚Äôve had zero luck, did like 100+ eternals‚Ä¶ not even 1 legendary, not even the ones that are bad. I do so little damage compared to characters with legendary that sometimes groups just kick me in the middle of the run and say that they‚Äôre sorry but I do no damage. luckily, this week on the economy update, I just bought a bunch of purple mithrils and rerolled boots for a bunch of times until I got that legendary at 255 ilvl. Now I‚Äôm having much more fun and my damage has improved tremendously. If it was my ‚Äòmain char‚Äô and not an alt, I might have been so frustrated by now that I‚Äôd take a break, might even quit.
2. In queues, there are often less tanks/healers compared to dps players, I think adding some kind of ''extra reward'' for in-demand roles may motivate more players to try out those roles.. for example, if there''s currently low amounts of tanks in queue, add a ''X bonus marks of fellowship'' for tanks, it might encourage more people to try different roles.
3. When I queue, current dungeon selection window pops-up and the entire screen is blurred.. I wish the chat window will stay visible and functional. it‚Äôs a team game, let us coordinate our selection. currently, a lot of times the dungeon being selected gets someone to leave, for example, 3 players pick a capstone, then when we‚Äôve loaded the map and we‚Äôre all in, tank types ‚ÄúI don‚Äôt have the time for capstone, sorry‚Äù and leaves‚Ä¶‚Ä¶and then I‚Äôm back to another 10 min of queue. If we had chat, he would write it in the selection window and we could have just picked something else or something.
4. the nameplates just feels broken on huge pulls. when there are more than 12-15 mobs in a pack, once they‚Äôre stacked together, seeing a cast go out is luck-based, it all depends on the way the order the nameplates stacked up, you can easily miss an important cast and wipe. I wish there was a way to manually choose priority mobs so they‚Äôre always shown OR just edit the nameplates and make mobs hp bar super thin and their cast bar larger.
5. Gem grind, do I need to ellaborate? I wish it would at least be account-wide.
6. Dungeon Codex, currently only shows gear drops, I wish it would show enemies spells, boss mechanics explanations and relevant dungeon information.
7. E20 and E40, what‚Äôs the actual difference between them? I wish the game would just show useful information about the levels, for example: E20: - Enemies have +1000% HP - Enemies deal +250% more damage E40: - Enemies have +2000% HP - Enemies deal +500% more damage
8. It may feel silly, but it‚Äôs 2025, why do we have to manually light-up campfires? Please make it so once the mobs surrounding it die, that check-point gets ac', 'Technology & Software', 'fellowshipgame', 2, 8, 0.8, '$0-$5M', 'online', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'open', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, FALSE, 'active', '2025-12-15 17:50:24.226892+00:00', '2025-12-15 23:01:44.302742+00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, TRUE, '2025-12-17 00:32:46.503861', 72, 'Feature request for niche indie game - not a business opportunity, game feedback post', '$0-$5M', 'high', 'low', 'Game developers seeking player feedback tools', 2, '["Player feedback aggregation platform for indie game studios", "Game analytics tool focusing on player retention and satisfaction metrics", "Community management SaaS for small game development teams"]', '["Could focus specifically on indie/small studio game development feedback loops", "Integration of sentiment analysis with actionable game design recommendations"]', '["This is player feedback, not a systemic business pain point", "Extremely niche - applies only to Fellowship game developers", "Low validation (8 upvotes) indicates minimal broader pain", "Game feedback tools already exist (Discord, Reddit, Steam reviews, PlaytestCloud)", "Game studios already have established feedback channels"]', '["Do NOT pursue - this is individual game feedback, not a business opportunity", "If interested in gaming space, research systematic pain points across multiple studios", "Interview 20+ indie game developers about their feedback collection challenges"]', 'Community Feedback Analytics Platform for Game Developers', 'Game developers struggle to systematically collect, categorize, and prioritize player feedback from various sources. Players share valuable insights about what they love and want improved, but this feedback is scattered across forums, social media, and streams, making it difficult for developers to identify actionable patterns and prioritize improvements that matter most to their community.', '{"original_title" : "My top things I love about Fellowship alongside my top things I''d love to see improved", "original_body" : "It''s a personal list, I assume you all have your own lists, don''t be shy and share them in the comments!\n\nI love this game, love seeing it improve and gets better and better, I''m kind of hooked...  \nSo let''s start...\n\n**What I like? (sorted by best at the top)**\n\n1. Hamish streams and videos - this just has to be numero uno ü´°, he''s just really really friendly and positive, he''s the face of this game right now and he''s doing a great job.\n2. The progression system and leagues, that phase before hitting eternals feels very clear in terms of game progression, milestones are visible, gear upgrades, finishing a capstone in time and moving on to the next difficulty simply feels good and rewarding.\n3. It may feel dumb to ‚Äòlike‚Äô such a simple thing, but the Interrupt system is just amazing to me, no idea if there are other games that has implemented this in a similar/exact way or not, personally I didn‚Äôt see something like that anywhere else. the simplicity of me marking a target so everyone now knows ‚Äúokie, this one is taken care of‚Äù is just awesome.\n4. The dungeons, the art, boss fights, really really well done, I specifically like the capstone. I especially love Cithrel‚Äôs Fall and Wraithtide, I dig the fact that there are 3 bosses and I get to choose the order I get to tackle them, I can build my route the way I want.\n5. The patch cadence feels good, feels like the game is getting more than decent attention on a weekly basis.\n6. Attention to details, I have a bunch of examples, but let‚Äôs pick just one, to me, things like the hidden holiday bear mount shows the love for the game by the devs.\n\n**What I dislike and would love to see getting addressed and improved**  \n**(again sorted by my highest priority at the top)**\n\n1. No ‚Äòbad luck‚Äô protection in legendaries, in my eyes, this should be a top priority and relatively easy to address. legendaries have huge impact on your gameplay and damage/healing, it feels really really bad not getting your ‚Äòneeded‚Äô legendary. For example, my main is Helena, I had amazing luck and got the exact legendary that I‚Äôve wanted after a few champion dungeons runs.. it felt great. but on my Mara, the only viable legendary right now are the boots, the boots provide incredible gains to energy regeneration and damage, the two other legendaries are trash in comparison‚Ä¶. And I‚Äôve had zero luck, did like 100+ eternals‚Ä¶ not even 1 legendary, not even the ones that are bad. I do so little damage compared to characters with legendary that sometimes groups just kick me in the middle of the run and say that they‚Äôre sorry but I do no damage. luckily, this week on the economy update, I just bought a bunch of purple mithrils and rerolled boots for a bunch of times until I got that legendary at 255 ilvl. Now I‚Äôm having much more fun and my damage has improved tremendously. If it was my ‚Äòmain char‚Äô and not an alt, I might have been so frustrated by now that I‚Äôd take a break, might even quit.\n2. In queues, there are often less tanks/healers compared to dps players, I think adding some kind of ''extra reward'' for in-demand roles may motivate more players to try out those roles.. for example, if there''s currently low amounts of tanks in queue, add a ''X bonus marks of fellowship'' for tanks, it might encourage more people to try different roles.\n3. When I queue, current dungeon selection window pops-up and the entire screen is blurred.. I wish the chat window will stay visible and functional. it‚Äôs a team game, let us coordinate our selection. currently, a lot of times the dungeon being selected gets someone to leave, for example, 3 players pick a capstone, then when we‚Äôve loaded the map and we‚Äôre all in, tank types ‚ÄúI don‚Äôt have the time for capstone, sorry‚Äù and leaves‚Ä¶‚Ä¶and then I‚Äôm back to another 10 min of queue. If we had chat, he would write it in the selection window and we could have just picked something else or something.\n4. the nameplates just feels broken on huge pulls. when there are more than 12-15 mobs in a pack, once they‚Äôre stacked together, seeing a cast go out is luck-based, it all depends on the way the order the nameplates stacked up, you can easily miss an important cast and wipe. I wish there was a way to manually choose priority mobs so they‚Äôre always shown OR just edit the nameplates and make mobs hp bar super thin and their cast bar larger.\n5. Gem grind, do I need to ellaborate? I wish it would at least be account-wide.\n6. Dungeon Codex, currently only shows gear drops, I wish it would show enemies spells, boss mechanics explanations and relevant dungeon information.\n7. E20 and E40, what‚Äôs the actual difference between them? I wish the game would just show useful information about the levels, for example: E20: - Enemies have +1000% HP - Enemies deal +250% more damage E40: - Enemies have +2000% HP - Enemies deal +500% more damage\n8. It may feel silly, but it‚Äôs 2025, why do we have to manually light-up campfires? Please make it so once the mobs surrounding it die, that check-point gets ac", "subreddit" : "r/technology_and_software", "upvotes" : 8, "comments" : 2, "platform" : "reddit", "url" : "", "confidence_score" : 0.85}', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL) ON CONFLICT (id) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO opportunities (id, title, description, category, subcategory, severity, validation_count, growth_rate, market_size, geographic_scope, country, region, city, completion_status, solution_description, solved_at, solved_by, feasibility_score, duplicate_of, author_id, is_anonymous, status, created_at, updated_at, source_id, source_url, source_platform, ai_analyzed, ai_analyzed_at, ai_opportunity_score, ai_summary, ai_market_size_estimate, ai_competition_level, ai_urgency_level, ai_target_audience, ai_pain_intensity, ai_business_model_suggestions, ai_competitive_advantages, ai_key_risks, ai_next_steps, ai_generated_title, ai_problem_statement, raw_source_data, latitude, longitude, demographics, search_trends, demographics_fetched_at) VALUES (90, 'Photographers & Videographers who use MacBook Pro, IPad Pro or both', 'I am looking to make the switch to Apple and with the price point of things, I have so many questions. I want to make sure I‚Äôm investing wisely and not into something that might not be totally necessary. I‚Äôm not new to photography as it‚Äôs been something I‚Äôve done for fun since I‚Äôve been a kid. However, I am looking to turn this into a career or at least a side hustle for now. Also, please be nice. It might become obvious that I am not super educated when it comes to the technical side of things, that‚Äôs why I‚Äôm here. I also have ADHD and making decisions like this are difficult. I over think every little thing and second guess my own intuition the majority of the time. I wish there was a way to create a poll over what‚Äôs better and maybe there is. But I don‚Äôt know how to do it. Anywayyy‚Ä¶

What I am looking for: 

Over all performance; speed, memory, storage -  For storage on the MacBook Pro specifically, do you think I can get by on 512GB or should I go for the 1TB? I‚Äôve had people tell me that the 1TB is excessive and takes a life time to fill up. But I‚Äôve also heard that it actually isn‚Äôt that much and can be filled up within 2 years, especially with photos and videos. I have also been told that the 1TB has faster processors- is that true? 

Longevity - If I‚Äôm investing into something like this, I want it to last for several years. That is also where the storage and memory comes in. Does that affect anything? Is one going to last me longer than the other? I obviously know that storage will eventually run out, but there are external things I can use for storage. 

Portability - I absolutely love the screen size of the 16 inch MacBook Pro, but I‚Äôve heard it‚Äôs not ideal to travel with like the 14 inch is. I visit family a lot and I‚Äôll be shooting a wedding in Maine in September. Something that I can take on the plane so I can edit would be ideal. So my question is‚Ä¶is the 16 inch MacBook Pro worth the hassle for the screen size alone? 

The goal is to get both the MacBook Pro and the iPad Pro. The MacBook for the main things and iPad for editing specifically. They will primarily be used for photo editing, video editing and I would like to get into creating digital art. I will also eventually be using this for online classes when I go back to school and promoting my work. 

One thing that I have found with my own research is that the iPad Pro with the magic keyboard essentially becomes like a MacBook. If I were to get the iPad Pro, 13inch, 2TB of storage with the magic keyboard‚Ä¶do you think I could bypass getting the MacBook for now and be able to accomplish everything that I am wanting? The amount of content creation isn‚Äôt going to be too insane for the first year and I know that I can get an adapter to plug into the iPad to upload my photos. I also won‚Äôt be starting classes for a while yet. 

Any advice you have would be greatly appreciated :) ', 'Technology & Software', 'ipad', 1, 3, 0.3, '$10M-$50M', 'online', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'open', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, FALSE, 'active', '2025-12-15 17:50:24.226892+00:00', '2025-12-15 23:05:57.785184+00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, TRUE, '2025-12-17 00:32:51.484112', 72, 'Decision-support tool for creative professionals making complex tech purchasing decisions', '$10M-$50M', 'high', 'medium', 'Emerging creative professionals (photographers/videographers) transitioning to professional equipment', 6, '["Subscription-based decision engine ($9.99/month) with personalized gear recommendations based on workflow analysis", "Affiliate-driven free tool that recommends optimal configurations with purchase links to Apple/B&H/Adorama", "Freemium mobile app with interactive quiz, community voting, and premium 1-on-1 consultations ($49-$99)"]', '["Focus on neurodivergent-friendly decision-making (reducing analysis paralysis for ADHD users)", "Workflow-based recommendations vs spec-focused comparisons (matches needs to real use cases)", "Community validation feature allowing users to poll others with similar needs"]', '["Highly competitive space with existing YouTube channels, Reddit communities, and retail advisors providing free advice", "Limited to Apple ecosystem initially, which has strong in-house Genius Bar consultation already", "Rapid product cycle obsolescence requires constant content updates and maintenance", "Low validation (3 upvotes, 1/5 severity) suggests narrow problem scope"]', '["Survey 100+ emerging creative professionals about tech purchasing anxiety and willingness to pay for decision support", "Create MVP quiz/decision tree tool and test with photography/videography communities on Reddit, Facebook groups", "Analyze existing solutions (YouTube tech reviewers, B&H buying guides, Apple consultations) to identify specific gaps", "Interview 20 users who recently made similar purchases to understand decision-making process and pain points", "Test affiliate revenue potential by creating content-based recommendations and tracking conversion rates"]', 'Apple Device Decision Guide for Creative Professionals', 'Aspiring and hobbyist photographers/videographers struggle to decide between MacBook Pro and iPad Pro investments, especially those with ADHD who face decision paralysis. They need clarity on which device best suits their creative workflow and budget without overspending on unnecessary features.', '{"original_title" : "Photographers & Videographers who use MacBook Pro, IPad Pro or both", "original_body" : "I am looking to make the switch to Apple and with the price point of things, I have so many questions. I want to make sure I‚Äôm investing wisely and not into something that might not be totally necessary. I‚Äôm not new to photography as it‚Äôs been something I‚Äôve done for fun since I‚Äôve been a kid. However, I am looking to turn this into a career or at least a side hustle for now. Also, please be nice. It might become obvious that I am not super educated when it comes to the technical side of things, that‚Äôs why I‚Äôm here. I also have ADHD and making decisions like this are difficult. I over think every little thing and second guess my own intuition the majority of the time. I wish there was a way to create a poll over what‚Äôs better and maybe there is. But I don‚Äôt know how to do it. Anywayyy‚Ä¶\n\nWhat I am looking for: \n\nOver all performance; speed, memory, storage -  For storage on the MacBook Pro specifically, do you think I can get by on 512GB or should I go for the 1TB? I‚Äôve had people tell me that the 1TB is excessive and takes a life time to fill up. But I‚Äôve also heard that it actually isn‚Äôt that much and can be filled up within 2 years, especially with photos and videos. I have also been told that the 1TB has faster processors- is that true? \n\nLongevity - If I‚Äôm investing into something like this, I want it to last for several year